David Sacks on Yelen not bailing out SVB
SVB: Not a bailout, but all depositors must be made whole
text:
Let's not forget history. The world, not just the US, cannot afford "run on banks". We thought that we took care of that long time ago, but I guess this needs to be reiterate.

Depositors to SVB cannot lose their money, not even once cent. If this were to happen the general public will lose trust in the entire US banking system, and we will see a rise of true private banks, outside the FDIC system, and that would create a separate parallel monetary system. And who would control that?

The logical answer is some entity outside the US. China?

Only by making all the depositors whole we can assure reinforcing trust in the US banking system.

I am not saying to give a free pass, quite the opposite.

Starting with KPMG, the auditors of record, responsibility must be sought, and those individuals banned from the banking industry, and lobbying industry too, for the lifetime.

End of story.

title: Ask HN: Those who are not in a regular job what is your source of income?
text:
Did you leave your 9 to 5 job after your side venture paid off? Or did you never went for a regular job?

Ask HN: Small scripts, hacks and automations you're proud of?
text:
I sometimes think back fondly of the small automation scripts I wrote over the years, so I wanted to ask you: Which scripts, hacks & automations did you create that your're proud of? Personally, I built a bot to automatically answer apartment ads [1], a small script to run Borg backup once per day [2], and a small automation to track the temperature in my aquarium [3].
